# Tiny Compact Logging Practices for Texas Hold'em Poker Application

## Overview
Ultra-compact, information-dense logging using full words (no abbreviations) that maximizes useful data per character while maintaining readability.

## Core Principles

### üéØ Density First
- Every log line must contain maximum actionable information
- Use full words, not abbreviations
- Combine related data points in single lines
- Eliminate redundant words and formatting

### üìä Context Compression
- Use short, descriptive words for states (preflop, flop, turn, river)
- Compress IDs to first 6 chars when safe
- Use action words (bet, fold, call, raise, allin)
- Combine multiple events in one line when related

## Ultra-Compact Format

### Standard Format
```
[LEVEL] Time Component: Event | Data1:Value1 Data2:Value2 Data3:Value3
```

### Examples
```
