## Best Practices for Compact Logging

### Do's
- Use full words consistently across all components
- Combine related events in single lines
- Use descriptive action words
- Include essential context in every log
- Use short, meaningful component names
- Compress IDs and numbers where safe

### Don'ts
- Don't use abbreviations or acronyms
- Don't separate related data across multiple lines
- Don't include redundant information
- Don't use verbose error messages
- Don't log without essential context
- Don't use inconsistent word choices

